==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sluggard
<hw>Slug"gard</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Slug</ets> +
<ets>-ard</ets>.]</ety> <def>A person habitually lazy, idle, and
inactive; a drone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Go to the ant, thou <qex>sluggard</qex>; consider her ways, and be
wise.</q> <rj><qau>Prov. vi. 6.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sluggard</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sluggard
<hw>Slug"gard</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Sluggish; lazy.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sluggardize</ent>⟦br⟧
